A,B\in M_n(\mathbb{C})
A
AB=BA
A^*B=BA^*
p=p(x)=\sum_{k=0}^mc_kx^k
p(D)=D^*
D=\mathrm{diag}(\lambda_1,\ldots,\lambda_n)
p(D)=\mathrm{diag}\big(p(\lambda_1),\ldots,p(\lambda_n)\big)
\lambda_j
\overline{\lambda}_j
AB=BA
A^kB=BA^k
p(A)B=Bp(A)
 p(A)=\sum_{k=0}^m c_kA^k=\sum_{k=0}^m c_k(P^*DP)^k=\sum_{k=0}^m c_kP^*D^kP=P^*\left(\sum_{k=0}^m c_kD^k\right)P\\=P^*p(D)P=P^*D^*P=A^*. 
A^*B=p(A)B=Bp(A)=BA^*.
